.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-regex_lab \- Live regex tester: pattern + sample text, prints matches, named captures,
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility regex_lab
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Live regex tester: pattern + sample text, prints matches, named captures,
.SH BACKENDS (AUTO-DETECTED)
.PP
.IP \(em 4
\fBperl\fP — preferred, full PCRE support
.IP \(em 4
\fBgrep -P\fP — fast for simple extraction
.IP \(em 4
\fBpython3\fP — PCRE fallback with capture support
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
regex '\\d+' 'hello 42 world 99'
regex -p '\\w+' -f /var/log/syslog
regex -p 'foo(bar)' -s 's/foo(bar)/baz$1/' -t 'foobar qux'
echo 'abc123' | regex -p '[a-z]+' -i
.EE
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Flag   |   Meaning   |   Default
\fC-p, --pattern PAT\fP   |   Regex pattern   |   —
\fC-t, --text TEXT\fP   |   Sample text (or positional)   |   —
\fC-f, --file FILE\fP   |   Read text from FILE   |   —
\fC-i, --stdin\fP   |   Read text from stdin   |   —
\fC-s, --sub SUB\fP   |   Substitution expression   |   —
\fC-m, --multiline\fP   |   Multiline anchors   |   off
\fC-c, --case-insensitive\fP   |   Case-insensitive   |   off
\fC--color\fP   |   Colorize matches   |   off
\fC--json\fP   |   Machine-readable output   |   off
\fC--no-color\fP   |   Disable ANSI   |   off
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Matches found (or substitution applied)
\fC1\fP   |   No matches
\fC2\fP   |   Argument / dependency error
